definition.value: This is an AE which is a condition arising from an abnormal immune response to a functioning body part.
This is an AE which is a state of unresponsiveness of the immune system to substances or tissue that have the capacity to elicit an immune response in a given organism.
This is an AE which is immune-mediated inflammation or swelling of the muscles.

This is an AE which is a type of autoimmune myopathy characterized by relatively severe proximal weakness, myofiber necrosis with minimal inflammatory cell infiltrate on muscle biopsy, and infrequent extra-muscular involvement.
This is an AE which describes general immune-mediated inflammation of lung tissue.
This is an AE which is an immune disorder characterized by recurrent infections and low antibody levels, specifically in immunoglobulin (Ig) types IgG, IgM and IgA.
This is an AE which is a rare, benign and self-limited disease, affecting mainly young women and presenting with localised lymphadenopathy, fever and leucopenia in the majority of the reported cases.
This is an AE which is types of lymphoma affecting B cells.
This is an AE which is types of lymphoma affecting B cells and it is recurrent.
This is an AE which is a long-term autoimmune disorder that primarily affects joints.
This is an AE which may present with a clinical pattern of vesicles indistinguishable from dermatitis herpetiformis, or with vesicles and bullae in a bullous pemphigoid-like appearance.
This is an AE which is autoimmune diseases which primarily affect the body system.
This is an AE which is a condition arising from an abnormal immune response to a functioning endocrine part.

This is an AE which is a chronic disease in which the body interprets the thyroid glands and its hormone products T3, T4 and TSH as threats, therefore producing special antibodies that target the thyroid's cells, thereby destroying it.
This is an AE which is autoimmune inflammation of the kidneys and may involve the glomeruli, tubules, or interstitial tissue surrounding the glomeruli and tubules.

This is an AE which is an increasingly recognized type of chronic pancreatitis that can be difficult to distinguish from pancreatic carcinoma but which responds to treatment with corticosteroids, particularly prednisone.
This is an AE which is the most frequent cause of acquired thyroid dysfunction, most commonly presenting either as Hashimoto's thyroiditis or Graves' Disease.
This is an AE which refers not produce autoantibodies or antigen-specific T or B cells and can be characterized by errors in the innate immune system.
This is an AE which is a rare form of cancerous lymphoma affecting T-cells.
This is an AE which is a disease of the lymph nodes on the vaccination site , in which they are abnormal in size or consistency.
This is an AE which refers to a group of non-Hodgkin lymphomas in which aberrant T cells proliferate uncontrollably.
This is an AE which is a cancer of the lymphatic system, particularly B lymphocytes found in the germinal center.
This is an AE which is malformations of the lymphatic system characterized by lesions that are thin-walled cysts; these cysts can be macroscopic, as in a cystic hygroma, or microscopic.
This is an AE which is a cancer of B cells, a type of lymphocyte that is responsible for producing antibodies.
This is an AE which may arise as a consequence of the transformation of the underlying indolent lymphoma.

This is an AE which can be classified as noninfectious GLA and infectious GLA, noninfectious GLA includes sarcoidosis and sarcoid-like reaction and  infectious GLA can be classified as suppurative lymphadenitis (LA) and nonsuppurative LA.
This is an AE which is a disease of the lymph nodes on the injection site, in which they are abnormal in size or consistency.
This is an AE which is a heterogeneous group of lymphomas that derive from the malignant transformation of marginal zone B-cells.

This is an AE which represents a group of diseases characterized by non-granulomatous inflammation and necrosis of the lymph node, caused by a variety of infective and inflammatory diseases, most common being Kikuchi-Fujimoto disease, acute Epstein Barr viral infection and systemic lupus erythematosis .
This is an AE which is irregularities in the heartbeat, including when it is too fast or too slow and is nodal.

label.value: nodal marginal zone b-cell lymphoma AE

definition.value: This is an AE which is a group of clinically indolent B-cell lymphomas postulated to derive from memory B lymphocytes in the 'marginal zone' of secondary lymphoid tissue.
This is an AE which is a type of nodal osteoarthritis degenerative joint disease that results from breakdown of joint cartilage and underlying bone.
This is an AE which is a group of blood cancers that includes all types of lymphomas except Hodgkin lymphomas.
This is an AE which is a heterogeneous group of clinically aggressive diseases associated with poor outcome.
This is an AE which is a reactive lymphadenitis affecting HIV-positive patients; furthermore, PGL is often a prodrome of AIDS-related complex and AIDS.
This is an AE which is a high-grade neoplasm arising from precursor lymphocytes of B-cell lineage.

This is an AE which is inherited defects of the innate or adaptive arms of the immune system that lead to an increase in the incidence, frequency, or severity of infections and/or immune dysregulation.

label.value: primary mediastinal large b-cell lymphoma AE

definition.value: This is an AE which is a rare type of lymphoma that forms in the mediastinum (the space in between the lungs) and predominantly affects young adults.
This is an AE which is a benign lymphocytic infiltrate that resembles cutaneous lymphoma histologically, clinically, or both.
This is an AE which is a genetic immunodeficiency, a type of hypogammaglobulinemia.

This is an AE which is frequent, both as an apparently isolated defect (about one fourth of patients suffering otherwise unexplained repeated infections) and in association with a number of primary and required immunodeficiency states.
This is an AE which is a poorly defined dysgammaglobulinemia characterized by decreased levels of IgM while levels of other immunoglobulins are normal.
This is an AE which is one that affects a number of organs and tissues, or affects the body as a whole.
This is an AE which is an inflammatory state affecting the whole body.

This is an AE which is a highly heterogeneous disorder, characterized by differences in autoantibody profile, serum cytokines, and a multi-system involvement commonly affecting the skin, renal, musculoskeletal, and hematopoetic systems clinical manifestations involving.

This is an AE which is a type of mast cell disease, is a rare disorder affecting both children and adults caused by the accumulation of functionally defective mast cells (also called mastocytes) and CD34+ mast cell precursors.
This is an AE which is a rare but potentially life-threatening bleeding disorder characterized by autoantibodies directed against coagulation factor VIII.
This is an AE which is a spectrum of conditions caused by infection with the human immunodeficiency virus (HIV), a retrovirus.
This is an AE which is a generic term referring to a disorder in which a cyst or cavity forms within the spinal cord .
This is an AE which is an established treatment modality for a variety of hematologic malignancies.
